Article_Name: Odisha Registers 78.3% Polling In Second Phase Local Body Elections
News Info: Odisha has registered 78.3 per cent voting in the second phase of the polling for the three-tier panchayat elections, an official at the State Election Commission (SEC) said on Saturday.

Article_Name: "Shouldn't Have Dragged My Mother Into...": Priyanka Gandhi Slams BJP
News Info: The Congress General Secretary also accused the BJP of misleading the people by keeping them busy with divisive agendas in an attempt to get away with misgovernance and lack of development.

Article_Name: Ex-AAP Leader Kumar Vishwas Gets High Security After Arvind Kejriwal Row
News Info: The Centre on Saturday decided to give 'Y' category security to former leader of Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) Kumar Vishwas, official sources said.

Article_Name: Four More Towers At Gurugram Society Declared Unfit For Living
News Info: Days after several houses at Chintels Paradiso in Gurugram collapsed, the Department of Town and Country Planning has declared four more apartment towers unfit for living, leaving many residents in limbo.

Article_Name: 14-Year-Old Girl's Decomposed Body Found Inside Delhi Shop
News Info: The body of a 14-year-old girl was found inside a shop in the Narela area of the outer North District of Delhi on Saturday, police said.

Article_Name: Arvind Kejriwal Video Prompts Police Case Order By Punjab Poll Officer
News Info: A police case has been filed against Arvind Kejriwal and his Aam Aadmi Party or AAP for a video, which the poll body says makes "false and frivolous allegations against other parties" and violates the model code of conduct in Punjab

Article_Name: At BJP Rally In UP, Rajnath Singh Faces Angry Slogans Over Jobs
News Info: A campaign speech by Defence Minister Rajnath Singh in Uttar Pradesh's Gonda was interrupted by slogan-shouting men from the stands seeking jobs, specifically in the Indian Army.

Article_Name: Russian Troops "Poised To Strike" Ukraine: US Defence Chief
News Info: Russian troops on Ukraine's border are "uncoiling" and "poised to strike", US Secretary of Defense Lloyd Austin said on Saturday during a visit to Lithuania.

Article_Name: Watch: Punjab BJP Chief's "Vote-For-Congress" Appeal, Then Clarification
News Info: If you are not voting for the BJP, vote for the Congress, but certainly not the Aam Aadmi Party, the Punjab BJP chief had said at a poll campaign rally. Then came a hasty clarification.

Article_Name: Amid Ukraine Tensions, Russia Launches Ballistic Missiles In Exercises
News Info: Russia on Saturday successfully test-fired its latest hypersonic, cruise and nuclear-capable ballistic missiles as part of "planned exercises," the Kremlin said, as tensions soar over Ukraine.

Article_Name: Positive Results In Phase 3 Trial Of Covid Pill, Says Hetero Pharma Group
News Info: Drug firm Hetero on Saturday announced positive results of Phase III trials of Movfor (Molnupiravir), an investigational oral antiviral COVID-19 medicine.

Article_Name: "We Are Your Baap": Sena Warns BJP Minister After He Teases Notice Threat
News Info: The BJP-Sena slugfest has intensified recently with Mr Raut and Mr Somaiya both claiming to have evidence of corruption and extortion against each other's parties.

Article_Name: Russian President Putin Launches Strategic Drills With Ballistic Missiles: Report
News Info: Russian President Vladimir Putin on Saturday launched strategic military drills involving ballistic missiles amid rising tensions over Ukraine, the Kremlin said.

Article_Name: "Stereotyping": Supreme Court Scraps Gender Cap On Maharashtra Bar Performers
News Info: The Supreme Court has scrapped the condition imposed by Maharashtra authorities that limited the number of female and male performers in orchestra bars to four each, saying rules based on gender stereotypes have no place in the society.

Article_Name: Man Arrested For Climbing Mumbai Airport Perimeter Wall
News Info: A 21-year-old man was apprehended by the CISF personnel on Saturday after he climbed up the perimeter wall of the hyper-sensitive Mumbai International Airport, officials said.
